6, "timestamp": 1772549176, "uploader_id": "48929634087", "uploader": "Ellie Sleightholm", "channel": "ellieinstem", "like_count": 6547, "comment_count": 121, "comments": [{"author": "sam_3.141592653589793238462643", "author_id": "72821389132", "id": "18077040737394635", "text": "Mathematic perfection", "timestamp": 1775749828}, {"author": "vanessa.h.q", "author_id": "6231654598", "id": "17913302841360650", "text": "Euler", "timestamp": 1775747530}, {"author": "jeaneahpaikruthling", "author_id": "44101046363", "id": "18164413906426523", "text": "🙌axiomatic", "timestamp": 1775650871}, {"author": "iamakashh_07", "author_id": "59172771025", "id": "18078338858133202", "text": "This equation is used very effectively in our real life, which is why it is also called the most beautiful equation in mathematics. 😍", "timestamp": 1775542705}, {"author": "aleenaannajames", "author_id": "745505276", "id": "18165849058420626", "text": "❤️ almost cried, your voice is ethereal and soothing, the brilliance resonates like a rhythmic dance !!!", "timestamp": 1775503727}, {"author": "biodigav1.0", "author_id": "5945908866", "id": "18087068981001542", "text": "It equals zero (nothing) because after all the struggle of the human existance , when people die, everything sums up to zero (nothing)", "timestamp": 1775460027}, {"author": "tingledale", "author_id": "2536746294", "id": "17937849153195447", "text": "Euler", "timestamp": 1775396145}, {"author": "a_m_0000000000000", "author_id": "66318041723", "id": "17882540688523163", "text": "And adding them we get Zero So zero is everything (but its nothing in leyman's lang ) its quite philosophical than mathematics", "timestamp": 1775154519}, {"author": "_nagaraju_guntupalli", "author_id": "11374400020", "id": "17880541260410170", "text": "🙂‍↔️", "timestamp": 1775036112}, {"author": "unpescador", "author_id": "4249151881", "id": "17988107798792761", "text": "Euler", "timestamp": 1774936459}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdn